description: Lists workflow build versions based on filtering parameters.

parameters.name: filters
parameters.description: Used to streamline search results. (dict) --- A filter name and value pair that is used to return a more specific list of results from a list operation. Filters can be used to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as tags, attributes, or IDs. name (string) --- The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive. values (list) --- The filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive. (string) ---

nested_params.name: name
nested_params.description: The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive.

nested_params.name: values
nested_params.description: The filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive.

nested_items.name: workflowVersionList
nested_items.description: A list of workflow build versions that match the request criteria.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the workflow resource.

nested_items.name: version
nested_items.description: The semantic version of the workflow resource. The format includes three nodes: <major>.<minor>.<patch>.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The image creation stage that this workflow applies to. Image Builder currently supports build and test stage workflows.

nested_items.name: owner
nested_items.description: The owner of the workflow resource.

nested_items.name: dateCreated
nested_items.description: The timestamp when Image Builder created the workflow version.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The next token used for paginated responses. When this field isn't empty, there are additional elements that the service hasn't included in this request. Use this token with the next request to retrieve additional objects.
